5D73367D.Line1.EECCF: The fly swarms plaguin’ us. We’ve done all we could: burnin’ corpses, coverin’ open water, rubbin' ourselves with gallowvine. Barely done any good.

915C2981.Line5.EECCF: Folk have had heavier worries on their minds, but the flies bit our last milkin’ cow to death.

F767AFFF.Line3.EECCF: The problem ain’t going away by ignorin’ it. I have some coin saved if ye can help with the infestation.
